WEBVTT

03:30.390 --> 03:32.510
- Honey, I'm home.
- Roger that.

03:32.600 --> 03:36.020
Copy at the boathouse.
Right on time.

03:36.140 --> 03:38.230
Faisil, get your butt in here.
Harry's inside.

03:39.350 --> 03:42.480
Yeah, yeah, I'm coming.
I'm coming.

03:45.480 --> 03:47.990
- Hey, were you born in a barn?
- Whorehouse.

03:53.160 --> 03:56.620
All right. You got
your fur-coated razor blade there...

03:56.700 --> 03:59.120
and a bunch of guys with guns.

04:02.710 --> 04:04.250
I'm switching to sub-vocal now.

04:05.710 --> 04:06.800
Check, check.

04:06.880 --> 04:08.720
- Check, check.
- It's talk radio.

04:08.800 --> 04:10.010
- You're on the air.
- Check.

04:26.440 --> 04:29.110
That guard nearest to you
is moving away.

04:36.990 --> 04:40.290
He's at the service door.
He's inside.

05:22.250 --> 05:23.750
Have you seen Khaled yet?

05:25.960 --> 05:28.170
Yep, there he is.

05:28.170 --> 05:30.300
How come billionaires
are always short?

05:35.720 --> 05:37.350
Excuse me.

05:37.350 --> 05:39.180
Thank you.

05:42.770 --> 05:45.020
Colonel! How are you?

05:45.100 --> 05:48.150
- It's so good to see you again.
- Yes, it's been a long time.

05:48.230 --> 05:50.320
- Terrific.
- Who was that guy?

05:52.740 --> 05:55.030
Could you hold this
for a second? Thanks.

05:56.160 --> 06:00.200
You should be crossing the main foyer,
heading for the stairs.

06:05.880 --> 06:08.170
Keep moving. Keep moving.

06:18.390 --> 06:22.060
I'm in the library, heading out
to the second-floor balcony.

07:16.490 --> 07:20.660
Modem in place.
Transmitting now.

07:20.740 --> 07:22.030
Affirmatory.

07:22.160 --> 07:24.950
It's a good hook-up.

07:25.040 --> 07:28.960
These are encrypted files.
It's going to take me a few minutes.

07:30.750 --> 07:32.960
I got your password.

08:12.500 --> 08:16.630
- Magnificent, isn't it?
- Yes, quite.

08:16.710 --> 08:20.340
I thought I knew Khaled's friends,
but I don't believe I've met you before.

08:20.430 --> 08:23.180
We haven't met,
because I certainly would remember.

08:23.300 --> 08:25.640
Renquist, Harry Renquist.

08:26.600 --> 08:29.520
-Juno Skinner.
-Juno Skinner.

08:31.810 --> 08:33.230
Come on!

08:33.860 --> 08:35.780
"Juno Skinner,
arts and antiquities dealer...

08:35.860 --> 08:38.320
specializing in ancient Persia."

08:38.400 --> 08:41.110
This is Persian,
if I'm not mistaken.

08:41.200 --> 08:45.240
Very good.
Sixth century BC, to be exact.

08:45.330 --> 08:48.960
- Do you like the period?
- I adore it.

08:57.380 --> 09:01.380
We got a problem.
Guards are going ape shit down there.

09:01.760 --> 09:03.510
Acquired most of these pieces
for Jamal.

09:05.100 --> 09:07.640
Do you tango?

09:08.140 --> 09:09.430
Tango?

09:09.430 --> 09:13.350
Harty, you do not have time
to tango, buddy.

09:13.350 --> 09:15.440
You copy?

10:02.950 --> 10:06.030
Don't be stopping to smell
the roses now. You hear me?

10:06.160 --> 10:09.330
- You gotta get out of there.
- Yes! Files are unlocked!

10:09.450 --> 10:12.080
Fast Faisil strikes again.
I'm in. I'm down, baby.

10:12.200 --> 10:14.790
I got my hand up her dress,
and I am going for the gold...

10:14.790 --> 10:16.710
Just copy the goddam files, okay?

10:46.450 --> 10:49.370
Wow. And I thought
this was just gonna be...

10:49.370 --> 10:52.580
another bunch of boring bankers
and oil billionaires.

10:52.790 --> 10:55.500
Seconds count.
Ditch the bitch.

10:55.500 --> 10:59.040
Unfortunately, I have to leave.

10:59.210 --> 11:01.130
I have a plane to catch.

11:03.300 --> 11:07.300
Well, call me sometime.

11:07.550 --> 11:09.890
My offices are in Rome.

11:09.890 --> 11:11.760
I would like that.

11:18.350 --> 11:22.690
Son of a bitch is with her two minutes,
and she's ready to bear his children.

11:22.980 --> 11:25.190
Twinkle toes,
what's your exit strategy?

11:25.280 --> 11:27.570
I'm going to walk
right out of the front gate.

11:27.660 --> 11:30.200
Ballsy. Stupid, but ballsy.

11:36.540 --> 11:40.250
Sir, may I see
your invitation, please?

11:40.330 --> 11:43.170
Sure. Here is my invitation.

11:50.720 --> 11:52.680
Shit. Here we go.

11:52.760 --> 11:54.350
Slight change in plans.

12:12.200 --> 12:13.910
Stay!

12:34.060 --> 12:36.220
We're en route to
the lower rendezvous point.

12:36.310 --> 12:37.980
Repeat, back-up rendezvous point!

12:39.560 --> 12:43.440
- Watch it!
- It's called ice, and it's slick.

13:00.870 --> 13:03.710
- Harry, do you copy? Whoa!
- I got it.

13:05.420 --> 13:06.170
Shit!

13:07.550 --> 13:08.670
Whoops!

13:54.050 --> 13:55.640
Oh, my God!

13:55.720 --> 13:57.810
Whoa! I got it!
I got it! I got it!

14:00.350 --> 14:01.560
- There he is!
- Shit!

14:02.640 --> 14:04.730
Hi, guys.

14:06.480 --> 14:09.690
That worked good.
Right out the old front gate.

14:09.780 --> 14:11.740
Can you lean back a second?

14:13.200 --> 14:15.870
Let's go.
We can still make our flight.

14:28.750 --> 14:33.220
All right, that's it
for Mr. Renquist. Okay, go.

14:33.300 --> 14:38.930
We got Harry Tasker billfold,
Harry Tasker passport, ticket stub.

14:39.060 --> 14:42.310
Hotel bill, Tasker.
I got two postcards here from Geneva.

14:44.100 --> 14:46.230
Got some house keys right there...

14:46.310 --> 14:49.770
and I've got a souvenir
Swiss snowing village.

14:49.860 --> 14:52.150
- What's that for?
- It's for Dana, stupe.

14:52.280 --> 14:54.610
Bring your kid home a gift,
the dad thing.

14:54.700 --> 14:55.820
Nice touch.

14:55.910 --> 14:59.580
- Pick me up tomorrow at 8:00.
- Will do.

15:02.080 --> 15:04.620
The debriefing is at 1000.

15:05.960 --> 15:07.830
- See you at 8:00. Bye.
- Hey, Harry.

15:07.920 --> 15:10.250
Did you forget something?

15:11.630 --> 15:14.050
What a team.

15:14.130 --> 15:16.430
Sleep fast, buddy.

15:54.920 --> 15:58.590
Hi, honey. How was your flight?

16:00.050 --> 16:02.390
- It was fine.
- Good.

16:16.860 --> 16:20.910
Brought you a little gift
from Switzerland. Snowy village.

16:20.990 --> 16:23.830
Wow. Thanks, Dad.

16:23.870 --> 16:26.370
- I've never had one of these.
- You're welcome.

16:26.450 --> 16:28.540
You're late for school.
You better get going.

16:28.620 --> 16:31.710
- Don't forget to feed Gizmo.
- Okay.

16:31.790 --> 16:34.420
It's pretty lame.

16:40.970 --> 16:42.850
- I'm late.
- Yeah, me too.

16:42.930 --> 16:46.390
How'd it go at the convention?
Make all the other salesmen jealous?

16:46.470 --> 16:49.230
It was fantastic.
You wouldn't believe it.

16:49.350 --> 16:51.980
You should have been there.
We were the big hit of the show.

16:52.060 --> 16:55.610
With that new model ordering system,
the 680 I told you about...

16:55.690 --> 16:57.990
I can write up an order
and immediately...

16:58.070 --> 17:01.780
as soon as the customer's name comes up,
you see what his credit line is...

17:01.860 --> 17:05.330
what he has ordered in the past,
what discount he has gotten.

17:05.410 --> 17:08.080
- Every little detail.
- Sounds great.

17:08.160 --> 17:10.920
It's fantastic. That's why
I love the computer business.

17:11.000 --> 17:13.000
Listen, the plumber called.

17:13.080 --> 17:17.590
He says he has to dig under the slab
or something that's gonna cost $600.

17:17.670 --> 17:21.260
- That's okay.
- It's not okay. It's extortion.

17:21.340 --> 17:23.340
What did you tell him?

17:23.430 --> 17:26.850
I slept with him and
he said he'd knock off $100.

17:26.930 --> 17:29.390
That's good thinking.
Bye, honey.

17:33.060 --> 17:34.810
Hello!

18:05.800 --> 18:08.810
Boy, I remember the first time
I got shot out of a cannon.

18:08.810 --> 18:12.060
- Good morning. Go to school.
- Yeah, I am.

18:15.060 --> 18:17.860
Thanks, dear.

18:17.860 --> 18:19.610
Check these out.

18:19.780 --> 18:21.150
Check them out.

18:21.400 --> 18:23.570
Where's the image coming from?

18:23.820 --> 18:27.580
Got a CCD camera and a transmitter
in a pack of smokes out there.

18:27.580 --> 18:29.540
It's pretty cool, huh?

18:32.540 --> 18:34.080
What the hell?

18:40.460 --> 18:42.590
Bye, Dad!

18:43.670 --> 18:46.890
- She's ripping you off.
- I knew it.

18:51.390 --> 18:53.560
Let's go!

18:53.730 --> 18:55.980
Can't stop! I'm late! Bye, Dad!

18:56.520 --> 18:58.360
God. Shit.

19:00.900 --> 19:03.900
Kids. Ten seconds of joy,
30 years of misery.

19:03.900 --> 19:06.860
I got married three times, but at least
I was never dumb enough to have any.

19:06.860 --> 19:10.410
She shouldn't be stealing.
I taught her better than that.

19:10.450 --> 19:12.580
You're not her parents any more,
you and Helen.

19:12.580 --> 19:14.710
Her parents are
Axl Rose and Madonna.

19:14.830 --> 19:18.630
Five minutes a day you spend with her
can't compete with that bombardment.

19:18.630 --> 19:20.250
You're outgunned, Daddy-o.

19:21.420 --> 19:23.590
It's not just
because you're a bad parent.

19:23.590 --> 19:25.970
Kids today are ten years ahead
of where we were at the same age.

19:26.180 --> 19:28.180
- Morning.
- Morning, Mr. Tasker.

19:28.390 --> 19:30.510
- I bet you think she's still a virgin.
- Don't be ridiculous.

19:30.510 --> 19:32.680
- She's only... What is she now?
- She's 14.

19:32.770 --> 19:36.060
- She's only 14.
- Her hormones are going like an alarm.

19:36.060 --> 19:38.230
It's even money she lets that physicist
on the bike boink her.

19:38.480 --> 19:40.190
- Not Dana.
- "Not Dana."

19:40.190 --> 19:43.110
Denial. It's not just a river
in Egypt no more, is it?

19:43.110 --> 19:45.530
She's probably stealing the money
to pay for an abortion.

19:45.530 --> 19:48.280
Why don't you open the door?

19:48.280 --> 19:50.200
Or drugs.

19:53.160 --> 19:56.210
Twenty here, 50 there. I figured
my wife's boyfriend was taking it.

19:56.210 --> 19:59.460
He takes everything else. There's
never a beer in the goddam fridge.

19:59.580 --> 20:01.920
- Thought you moved out.
- I had to move back in.

20:01.920 --> 20:04.920
My lawyer said it'd give me
a better shot at getting the house...

20:05.090 --> 20:07.590
during the property settlement,
but don't change the subject.

20:07.880 --> 20:10.640
- You still owe me 200 bucks.
- Good morning, Janice.

20:17.310 --> 20:21.860
- Good morning.
- Identify yourselves to the scanner.

20:21.860 --> 20:25.860
- Harry Tasker, 10024.
- Albert Gibson, 34991.

20:38.660 --> 20:43.290
All right, Frances. I don't believe
we need you any longer now. Thank you.

20:53.220 --> 20:57.480
Sweet Jesus. You sure screwed
the pooch last night, didn't you?

20:57.680 --> 21:02.610
Would you please tell me how I can see
this as anything but a total disaster?

21:02.610 --> 21:05.110
"Total" is a strong word.

21:05.110 --> 21:07.240
There are different
degrees of totality.

21:07.240 --> 21:10.610
It's a scale, really, with
a perfect mission on one end...

21:10.860 --> 21:13.870
and then a total pooch screw
on the other, and we're more on this...

21:14.160 --> 21:17.450
Faisil, you're new on Harry's team,
aren't you?

21:18.500 --> 21:19.830
Yes.

21:19.830 --> 21:25.380
So what makes you think the slack
I cut him in any way translates to you?

21:26.420 --> 21:28.590
Let me show you what we got.

21:31.090 --> 21:35.100
Jamal Khaled. We think he's dirty,
so we raid his private financial files.

21:37.310 --> 21:40.310
One hundred million in wire transfers
from the Commerce Bank International.

21:40.310 --> 21:43.270
Which is a front for certain countries
to finance terrorist activities.

21:43.440 --> 21:46.150
That's why we think
something really big is going down.

21:46.190 --> 21:48.400
We know that a week ago
four MIRV warheads were smuggled...

21:48.400 --> 21:50.360
out of the former
Soviet Republic of Kazakhstan.

21:50.360 --> 21:54.700
We think Khaled's group bought the nukes
and is trying to bring them to US soil.

21:54.740 --> 21:57.950
So far this is not
blowing my skirt up, gentlemen.

21:58.160 --> 22:01.750
Don't you have anything
remotely substantial?

22:01.870 --> 22:05.000
Harry, do you have any hard data?

22:05.000 --> 22:08.630
- Nothing you would call rock-hard.
- Actually it's pretty limp, sir.

22:08.840 --> 22:10.210
Then perhaps you better get some...

22:10.420 --> 22:12.970
before somebody parks an automobile
in front of the White House...

22:12.970 --> 22:16.100
with a nuclear weapon in the trunk.

22:16.180 --> 22:18.640
It's not like
he's saving the world or anything.

22:18.890 --> 22:21.390
He's a sales rep, for Christ's sake.

22:21.390 --> 22:24.350
Whenever I can't sleep,
I ask him to tell me about his day.

22:24.520 --> 22:26.900
Six seconds and I'm out.

22:27.020 --> 22:29.980
He acts like he's curing cancer
or something.

22:30.030 --> 22:32.280
I guess this means you didn't
get away for the weekend after all.

22:32.610 --> 22:35.110
- Harry had to go out of town.
- I'm shocked.

22:35.110 --> 22:37.330
Yeah, well, you know Harry.

22:39.910 --> 22:43.160
- What's up?
- Check this out.

22:43.160 --> 22:47.340
There's a $2 million disbursement
from Khaled to Juno Skinner.

22:47.500 --> 22:49.550
That's right.
The babe at the party.

22:51.960 --> 22:55.300
That doesn't mean anything.
She buys antiquities for Khaled.

22:55.380 --> 22:58.720
He keeps his antique buys
on a completely separate ledger.

22:58.800 --> 23:01.350
This is a little above market rate
for the horizontal bop...

23:01.430 --> 23:03.810
even for a total biscuit
like her.

23:03.890 --> 23:06.230
I want a complete work up on her.

23:06.310 --> 23:09.150
- Do we know where she is?
- Right here in River City.

23:09.270 --> 23:11.980
She lives in Rome, but she does stuff
for the Smithsonian.

23:12.070 --> 23:15.150
She has a lot of diplomatic connections,
so she has offices here.

23:15.240 --> 23:17.700
I guess it's time
to send in a specialist.

23:19.330 --> 23:22.370
- Care to tango?
- Yes, I would.

23:26.710 --> 23:28.460
Assholes.

23:32.760 --> 23:37.090
It's all set up. You got a fax machine,
ghost phones, all the usual stuff.

23:37.180 --> 23:41.010
You have a suite at the Marquis Hotel
under the name of Renquist.

23:41.100 --> 23:43.220
Reality check. Let's go.

23:43.310 --> 23:47.810
My name is Harry Renquist. I own
an art consulting firm in San Francisco.

23:47.980 --> 23:50.020
I have an appointment
with Miss Skinner.

23:50.110 --> 23:52.280
- Harry!
- Hello.

23:52.360 --> 23:53.820
Hello.

23:53.900 --> 23:56.950
I thought I'd see you again.
I just didn't know it would be so soon.

23:57.070 --> 24:00.120
- What's the point of waiting?
- I agree.

24:02.660 --> 24:06.830
Your clients are looking for something
for the lobby of their new headquarters?

24:06.910 --> 24:09.080
They would like to see something
very dramatic.

24:09.170 --> 24:11.170
That's a nice piece.

24:11.290 --> 24:15.170
I talked to a number of people,
and they all said you're the one to see.

24:15.340 --> 24:18.300
Really? Checking on me.

24:18.470 --> 24:22.430
So what did these people
say about me exactly?

24:22.560 --> 24:26.980
That you can read ancient Sanskrit
without having to sound out the words...

24:27.060 --> 24:31.400
and other art dealers and archaeologists
don't like you very much.

24:32.440 --> 24:34.150
Those wimps.

24:34.230 --> 24:38.450
It's because I use my diplomatic
contacts to export cultural treasures...

24:38.530 --> 24:41.620
from countries which tell them
to take a hike.

24:47.040 --> 24:49.790
Most of our pieces
come from ancient Persia.

24:49.870 --> 24:54.880
Unfortunately, ancient Persia is 20 feet
under the sand of Iran, Iraq and Syria.

24:55.000 --> 24:57.720
Not the most popular places
lately.

24:58.760 --> 25:02.720
So I've had to become an expert
in international diplomacy.

25:06.220 --> 25:07.560
Well, Mr. Renquist?

25:09.140 --> 25:11.940
Do you see anything you like?

25:12.020 --> 25:14.230
Maybe.

25:14.360 --> 25:18.280
Give me a break. I don't think
they bugged my tuna sandwich.

25:18.360 --> 25:20.450
She's importing stuff
from all over the Mideast.

25:20.570 --> 25:22.410
She could be moving
money, guns, anything.

25:22.570 --> 25:24.740
The second you left, we started
getting calls to the ghost numbers.

25:24.830 --> 25:26.830
They were checking out
the Renquist front.

25:26.910 --> 25:29.710
Let's step up the surveillance
and put on two more guys.

25:29.750 --> 25:33.790
Maurizio, I said Saturday,
not Tuesday. Saturday.

25:37.920 --> 25:41.260
Miss Skinner, may I have
a word with you, please?

25:51.350 --> 25:55.020
Stupid, undisciplined bitch.

25:55.110 --> 25:58.190
It's a good thing
you're paying me a lot of money.

25:59.320 --> 26:03.450
Do you realize there are surveillance
teams watching this place right now?

26:03.530 --> 26:05.830
Your telephones are
almost certainly tapped.

26:05.910 --> 26:10.370
And you were busy laughing and flirting
like a whore with this Renquist...

26:10.500 --> 26:12.710
He checked out okay...

26:13.540 --> 26:16.090
We do not tolerate mistakes.

26:20.670 --> 26:22.720
What would you like me to do?

26:22.800 --> 26:25.180
Find out where this Renquist is.

26:26.180 --> 26:28.310
Hello, Tektel Systems.
Mr. Tasker's office.

26:28.390 --> 26:31.020
Hi, Charlene? Hi, it's Helen.
Is he in?

26:31.100 --> 26:34.730
Harry's in a sales meeting, Mrs. Tasker.
Let me try him in there. Hold, please.

26:35.900 --> 26:38.020
Relay, 10024.

26:39.610 --> 26:42.150
It's a patch from Tektel.

26:42.900 --> 26:44.860
It's Helen.

26:44.950 --> 26:47.660
Hello, honey. How are you?
What's going on?

26:47.740 --> 26:50.410
Hi. I'm sorry to bother you
in the middle of a meeting.

26:50.490 --> 26:53.370
It's just that Dana and I want to make
sure you were gonna be home by 8:00.

26:53.460 --> 26:55.750
We're going to a lot of trouble
for your big birthday.

26:55.830 --> 26:59.550
We just wanted to make sure
that you were gonna be home.

26:59.630 --> 27:01.840
Absolutely.
This time you can count on me.

27:01.920 --> 27:03.260
- Promise?
- Trust me.

27:03.340 --> 27:05.130
- Great.
- Got to go. Bye.

27:05.220 --> 27:06.180
Bye.

27:06.260 --> 27:09.470
- That's disgusting, Dana.
- Calm down.

27:11.930 --> 27:15.900
We got a friend.
Three cars back on the inside lane.

27:16.020 --> 27:19.320
They've been on us
since we left the hotel.

27:19.400 --> 27:21.400
- You mean the station wagon?
- Yes.

27:21.480 --> 27:25.530
- You want me to lose them?
- No. We need this lead.

27:25.610 --> 27:26.610
Unit Seven?

27:28.280 --> 27:29.450
Seven here.

27:29.530 --> 27:32.080
We need you at the Georgetown Mall
in three minutes.

27:32.160 --> 27:35.620
- Copy. We're rolling.
- Helen's gonna be pissed.

27:36.290 --> 27:38.710
This is the problem with terrorists.

27:38.790 --> 27:41.840
They're really inconsiderate
when it comes to people's schedules.

27:52.310 --> 27:54.480
Pull over here. This is good.

27:58.940 --> 28:02.280
- Okay, testing, one, two, three.
- I got you. I got you. I got you.

28:06.570 --> 28:09.070
They're right with us.
I make three of them in the car.

28:20.710 --> 28:23.170
- Dick head.
- Blow me.

28:39.690 --> 28:42.020
I got a couple of them getting out
of the car and coming after you.

28:42.150 --> 28:43.900
Think I'm blind?

28:43.980 --> 28:47.990
You do look like Ray Charles.
So what's the plan?

28:48.070 --> 28:50.700
Just trying to get a closer look
at Beavis and Butt-head.

28:50.780 --> 28:54.200
- There's a third one still in the car.
- Stay on him.

29:16.470 --> 29:19.850
Hi, Helen. Yeah, it's Gib.
Oh, not much.

29:19.940 --> 29:23.190
Listen, Harry forgot something
back at the office.

29:23.270 --> 29:26.530
You know Harry.

29:26.610 --> 29:30.110
Yeah, Gib, I know Harry. Bye.

29:30.200 --> 29:31.570
Bye. See you soon.

29:32.700 --> 29:34.410
See?

30:17.030 --> 30:18.490
I lost the third guy.

30:58.120 --> 30:59.330
Shit!

31:04.250 --> 31:08.290
Shit! Hold it! Shit!

31:58.430 --> 32:01.100
Here. Cool off.

33:18.930 --> 33:21.550
Sorry about this.

33:27.350 --> 33:28.980
Look out! Get out of the way!

